1:52:05.969 --> 1:52:08.388
...but there's no way
I'm ready for that.

1:52:09.223 --> 1:52:13.184
PRIEST: A time to plant, and a time
to pluck up that which is planted.

1:52:13.352 --> 1:52:15.645
A time to kill and a time to heal.

1:52:16.021 --> 1:52:19.816
A time to break down
and a time to build up.

1:52:19.983 --> 1:52:23.486
A time to weep and a time to laugh.

1:52:23.654 --> 1:52:25.655
[SOBBING]

1:52:27.825 --> 1:52:30.785
PRIEST: A time to cast away stones....
CHAZZ: It's so senseless.

1:52:30.953 --> 1:52:32.870
Damn you, Roger.

1:52:35.833 --> 1:52:36.833
Roger.

1:52:37.084 --> 1:52:39.085
[CHAZZ CONTINUES SOBBING]

1:52:40.087 --> 1:52:42.088
Oh!

1:52:42.256 --> 1:52:44.132
Damn you, Roger!

1:52:44.299 --> 1:52:46.175
Damn it! Damn you!

1:52:46.343 --> 1:52:48.136
I'm in pain.

1:52:48.303 --> 1:52:50.888
Try to fight it. Try to fight it.

1:52:51.348 --> 1:52:53.266
I don't know about you people,
but I'm in pain.

1:52:53.434 --> 1:52:55.893
I know that there is no good in them...

1:52:56.061 --> 1:52:59.355
...for man to rejoice
and to do good in his life...

1:53:01.191 --> 1:53:04.986
...for that which befalleth
the sons of men, befalleth beasts.

1:53:06.071 --> 1:53:08.614
Even one thing befalleth...

1:53:08.782 --> 1:53:12.034
...as the one dieth, so dieth the other.

1:53:12.202 --> 1:53:14.662
Yea, they all have one breath...

1:53:14.830 --> 1:53:18.583
...so that a man hath no preeminence
above the beast.

1:53:19.293 --> 1:53:21.752
While each man thinks he knows love...

1:53:21.920 --> 1:53:25.673
...love, we have learned, is a mystery.

1:53:26.592 --> 1:53:30.136
That's what makes today so special.

1:53:31.889 --> 1:53:34.515
We witness two people
choosing to marry...

1:53:35.225 --> 1:53:38.895
...ones they truly love.

1:53:39.521 --> 1:53:40.897
[DOOR SLAMS]

1:53:46.320 --> 1:53:47.570
Whoa, whoa, hey!

1:53:47.738 --> 1:53:48.905
Hey! Hey!

1:53:51.408 --> 1:53:52.867
He's the best man.

1:53:55.329 --> 1:53:56.746
Yeah.

1:53:56.914 --> 1:53:58.915
Thank you.

1:54:15.265 --> 1:54:16.766
I don't believe this.

1:54:27.861 --> 1:54:29.237
Hat in hand.

1:54:29.404 --> 1:54:30.821
I'm sorry I'm late.

1:54:31.323 --> 1:54:33.324
I'm glad you're here.

1:54:33.492 --> 1:54:36.702
And I'm sorry I called you white trash.
I didn't--

1:54:36.870 --> 1:54:39.539
-John, apology accepted.
-Okay.

1:54:39.706 --> 1:54:42.792
And I'm sorry I called you a hillbilly,
I don't even know what that meant.

1:54:42.960 --> 1:54:45.044
John, it's okay.

1:54:45.212 --> 1:54:46.879
Do you mind if I get married now?

1:54:47.047 --> 1:54:48.881
-No, go ahead.
- [MOUTHING] Okay.

1:54:50.217 --> 1:54:51.968
Hi, Todd.

1:54:53.971 --> 1:54:56.514
Although we may choose
whom we marry...

1:54:57.140 --> 1:54:58.599
-...we don't always choose....
-Psst.

1:54:58.767 --> 1:55:02.812
[WHISPERING] Claire, I'm not here to
bother you, I just came to be his best man.

1:55:02.980 --> 1:55:05.815
Don't worry about me.
Pretend I'm not here.

1:55:06.650 --> 1:55:07.817
[MOUTHING]
Okay.

1:55:08.860 --> 1:55:10.236
I'm not a nut.

1:55:13.115 --> 1:55:15.783
You look really pretty, by the way.
That's all I'm gonna say.

1:55:18.704 --> 1:55:20.538
I can't stop thinking about you.

1:55:20.706 --> 1:55:22.707
It's all I think about
and I don't know what to do.

1:55:22.874 --> 1:55:24.166
JEREMY: Ahem.
-I'm sorry.

1:55:26.837 --> 1:55:29.338
O'NEIL:
You see, love is mysterious....

1:55:29.506 --> 1:55:31.132
God, I miss you.

1:55:33.760 --> 1:55:35.595
[WHISPERING]
Okay, excuse me, I'm sorry.

1:55:37.264 --> 1:55:40.266
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Claire, hold it a second. Claire, Claire.

1:55:40.434 --> 1:55:42.518
Claire, will you wait just a second?

1:55:42.686 --> 1:55:46.939
All I wanted was a second alone
so I could try to explain things.

1:55:47.274 --> 1:55:49.025
But I've never gotten that chance.

1:55:50.193 --> 1:55:52.528
Maybe I don't deserve it.

1:55:52.696 --> 1:55:54.030
So here goes.

1:55:54.531 --> 1:55:59.327
For longer than I care to remember,
my business has been crashing weddings.

1:55:59.703 --> 1:56:01.829
I crashed weddings to meet girls.

1:56:01.997 --> 1:56:03.873
Business was good.

1:56:04.041 --> 1:56:06.042
I met a lot of girls.

1:56:06.209 --> 1:56:09.670
And it was childish, it was juvenile--

1:56:09.838 --> 1:56:11.297
And pathetic.

1:56:11.673 --> 1:56:15.426
Yeah, that's probably
the best word to describe it.

1:56:15.594 --> 1:56:18.304
But you know what?
It also led me to you.

1:56:18.889 --> 1:56:21.599
So it's hard for me
to completely regret it.

1:56:21.767 --> 1:56:25.561
And that person that you met back
at your folks' place, that was really me.

1:56:25.729 --> 1:56:29.106
Maybe not my name--
I'm John Beckwith, by the way.

1:56:29.274 --> 1:56:30.650
--or my job...

1:56:30.817 --> 1:56:32.401
...but the feelings we felt...

1:56:32.903 --> 1:56:36.697
...the jokes, the stupid laughs,
that was all me.

1:56:36.865 --> 1:56:39.575
I've changed. I've realized something.

1:56:39.743 --> 1:56:42.828
-I crashed a funeral earlier, and I--
-Wha...?

1:56:42.996 --> 1:56:44.038
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

1:56:44.206 --> 1:56:46.207
Oh, Jesus.

1:56:47.209 --> 1:56:50.002
It wasn't my idea.
I was basically dragged to it.

1:56:50.170 --> 1:56:53.839
I went with Chazz, who you forgot
to tell me is totally insane.

1:56:54.424 --> 1:56:58.302
He also might be a genius, because
it actually does work. He's cleaning up.

1:56:58.470 --> 1:57:00.930
CLAIRE: John.
-I'm sorry. I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

1:57:01.098 --> 1:57:02.556
That's neither here nor there.

1:57:02.724 --> 1:57:05.851
And I see this widow and she's a wreck.

1:57:06.019 --> 1:57:09.271
She's just lost the person
she loves the most in this world.

1:57:10.440 --> 1:57:13.734
And I realized we're all gonna
lose the people we love.

1:57:14.236 --> 1:57:16.487
That's the way it is.

1:57:16.655 --> 1:57:20.282
But not me, not right now.

1:57:20.450 --> 1:57:23.285
Because the person I love the most
is standing right here...

1:57:24.329 --> 1:57:26.455
...and I'm not ready to lose you yet.

1:57:26.957 --> 1:57:30.710
Claire, I'm not standing here
asking you to marry me.

1:57:30.877 --> 1:57:33.129
I'm just asking you...

1:57:33.296 --> 1:57:35.548
...not to marry him.

1:57:36.633 --> 1:57:37.925
And maybe take a walk.

1:57:38.093 --> 1:57:40.052
Take a chance.

1:57:41.096 --> 1:57:43.973
Wow. Wow!

1:57:45.559 --> 1:57:50.229
This congregation really doesn't care about
how depressing your life is, John, okay?

1:57:50.397 --> 1:57:54.400
Claire, baby, could you go back up
on the altar so we can have a wedding?

1:57:56.653 --> 1:57:58.654
I'm sorry.

1:57:59.114 --> 1:58:00.156
I am.

1:58:00.323 --> 1:58:01.782
SACK:
What?

1:58:03.160 --> 1:58:04.785
I can't marry you.

1:58:07.914 --> 1:58:09.832
[CHUCKLES]

1:58:10.000 --> 1:58:11.333
Secretary...

1:58:11.501 --> 1:58:14.170
...your daughter's a little....

1:58:16.882 --> 1:58:19.842
Sack, I've always liked you...

1:58:20.552 --> 1:58:24.847
...so I put up with your stories
about scallops and otters...

1:58:25.015 --> 1:58:28.350
...and it's all good because
you seemed to make her happy...

1:58:28.518 --> 1:58:31.228
...and that's what matters to me most.

1:58:31.396 --> 1:58:34.523
But this is her decision.

1:58:37.110 --> 1:58:39.653
I stand by my daughter.

1:58:39.821 --> 1:58:41.030
You don't know shit.

1:58:41.198 --> 1:58:43.365
-Claire, go back up on the altar.
-No.

1:58:43.533 --> 1:58:46.327
Claire! Claire, get up
on that altar right now.

1:58:46.495 --> 1:58:47.703
Stop it.

1:58:47.871 --> 1:58:49.997
Claire, get your fucking ass
on that altar right now!

1:58:50.165 --> 1:58:52.750
Wow, getting a nice preview
of what marriage is gonna be like...

1:58:52.918 --> 1:58:54.001
...with Ike Turner here.

1:58:56.046 --> 1:58:57.797
-Sack!
-Oh, God, here it goes.

1:58:57.964 --> 1:58:59.840
[GRUNTING]

1:59:00.008 --> 1:59:01.425
[PEOPLE SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

1:59:01.593 --> 1:59:03.803
Share that with the Dalai Lama, jackass.

1:59:05.889 --> 1:59:08.557
-I think I had him.
-I know you did.

1:59:08.725 --> 1:59:10.226
Just go kiss the broad.

1:59:12.813 --> 1:59:14.814
[MOANING]

1:59:21.488 --> 1:59:23.864
Would it be a total clich
if I kissed you right now?

1:59:25.242 --> 1:59:26.826
Yes.

1:59:35.877 --> 1:59:38.087
Just wonderful.

1:59:39.464 --> 1:59:42.007
So damn beautiful.

1:59:43.510 --> 1:59:45.886
With every death there comes rebirth.

1:59:46.054 --> 1:59:48.138
-It's the circle of life.
-Oh.

1:59:49.266 --> 1:59:50.391
We're gonna be all right.

1:59:51.518 --> 1:59:53.227
Hey.

1:59:58.692 --> 2:00:00.651
[CRYING]

2:00:00.819 --> 2:00:02.319
Hey.

2:00:05.574 --> 2:00:06.949
[LAUGHING]

2:00:07.117 --> 2:00:09.743
-So, what's next?
-I'm starving.

2:00:09.911 --> 2:00:12.371
Fujimora wedding, 3 p.m.

2:00:12.539 --> 2:00:13.789
Hey, hey.

2:00:13.957 --> 2:00:16.709
I'm just throwing it out there.
I'm just saying, just....

2:00:18.128 --> 2:00:19.962
They would have great tempura.

2:00:20.130 --> 2:00:22.381
We don't even have a back-story,
I just....

2:00:22.549 --> 2:00:25.134
-No, forget it, forget it.
-I'm talking out loud.

2:00:26.303 --> 2:00:30.055
We're a folk-singing group
from Salt Lake City.

2:00:30.223 --> 2:00:32.099
Yeah.

2:00:32.434 --> 2:00:33.642
Yes, we are.

2:00:36.646 --> 2:00:38.647
[SCREAMING]

2:06:54.357 --> 2:06:56.358
Subtitles by
SDI Media Group

2:06:56.526 --> 2:06:58.527
[ENGLISH SDH]
